name: printed wiring board production, for power supply unit, desktop computer, Pb free | printed wiring board, for power supply unit, desktop computer, Pb free | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/1029/documentation

The data represent the PWB of a power supply unit, used in modern Desktop PCs. Material data are based on own dismantling activities. Infrastructure and production efforts are based on own assumptions.;This dataset represents the average composition and production efforts for 1 kg of a mounted PWB of a power supply unit (PSU), as used in a desktop PC. Main data are taken from own dismantling activities.

From reception of printed wiring board at the factory gate.

This dataset includess component input and production efforts (incl. PWB waste due to failure in mounting) for the production of a PWB used in the power supply unit of a desktop PC, using Pb-free solder material.
category: C:Manufacturing/26:Manufacture of computer, electronic and optical products/261:Manufacture of electronic components and boards/2610:Manufacture of electronic components and boards

processDocumentation.geographyDescription: Data represent a global valuable composition of PWB in a power supply unit.

exchanges.description:
The PCâ€™s power supply must accept a relatively high-voltage alternating current (AC) ranging in different countries from 100 to 240 V, and convert it into much lower voltage direct current (DC), which operates the electronic devices inside. Voltage variation outside the accepted standards can cause data errors or system crashes. The power supply runs all subsystems inside the system unit and is vital to the proper operation of any PC.
